Title: Why we all need subtitles now
Description:
It's not you ‚Äî the dialogue in TV and movies has gotten harder to hear.

Subscribe and turn on notifications üîî so you don't miss any videos: http://goo.gl/0bsAjO 

Have you ever been watching a show or movie, and then a character delivers a line so unintelligible you have to scramble to find the remote and rewind? For me, this moment came during the climax of the Pete Davidson film ‚ÄúThe King of Staten Island,‚Äù where his most important line was impossible to understand. 

I had to rewind three times ‚Äî and eventually put subtitles on ‚Äî to finally pick up what he was saying.

This experience isn‚Äôt unique ‚Äî gather enough people together and you can generally separate them into two categories: People who use subtitles, and people who don‚Äôt. And according to a not-so-scientific YouTube poll we ran on our Community tab, the latter category is an endangered species ‚Äî 57% of you said you always use subtitles, while just 12% of you said you generally don‚Äôt.
 
But why do so many of us feel that we need subtitles to understand the dialogue in the things we watch?

The answer to that question is complex ‚Äì and we get straight to the bottom of it in this explainer, with the help of dialogue editor Austin Olivia Kendrick.

Title: THE GREATEST QUOTES OF ALL TIME
Description:
Check out our store: https://becomingking.net/

When looking through history to find motivation and inspiration there's a wealth of material to draw from which made creating this video no easy task. My goal when selecting these quotes for narration was to choose the ones that had the biggest impact on me in the hope that they have a similar effect on you. 

Your list might be different and its been great to see your favourite quotes in the comments.  As we look back though history there's no denying that people faced extremely challenging times. Its filled with periods of incredible adversity in which some individuals managed to thrive in spite of. It's no wonder words of encouragement from history are not difficult to find. It never ceases to amaze me how applicable these are to the challenges we face today. 

We all face hardship in life but It's how we choose to respond to it that counts. I hope this video has at least one quote that speaks to you and your current situation. We forget how closely related we all are. It's often the case that the problems we believe are most personal to us are the ones that are the most commonly shared. We are not alone in this journey. 

Thanks for watching 

James 
  
Voice over by Chris Lines

Title: Beauty and the Beast Full Movie - Fairy Tales  With English Subtitles
Description:
#beauty #beast #fairytale #story #children #kids
#beautyandthebeastfullmovie

BEAUTY AND THE BEAST
Once upon a time there lived a wealthy merchant and his three daughters.
One day, the father was to go to a far-off place and he asked his daughters what they wanted on his return. The first and the second daughter asked for lovely dresses. But the third daughter, whose name was Beauty, said, ‚ÄúFather, I only need a rose plucked by your hand.‚Äù The merchant, on his way back, had to cross through the deep forest. It was dark and the merchant tried to find a place to sleep. He suddenly found a huge castle and went inside to find nobody. There was       a huge table with delicious food and he ate it all. Then the merchant went into the bedroom and slept on a soft and fluffy bed. The next day, too, the merchant did not find anyone in the castle. He saw a beautiful rose bush growing in the lawn and remembered Beauty‚Äôs gift. He plucked a red rose from the bush.
Suddenly, a ferocious looking beast sprang out of the bush. He was wearing fine silk clothes and roared, ‚ÄúI gave you food and a bed to sleep in! And now, you are stealing my roses!‚Äù The merchant was frightened and told the Beast about Beauty‚Äôs gift. The Beast decided to let him go only if he promised to send Beauty to this castle. The merchant agreed and ran back home. He cried and told his daughters about the Beast. But Beauty loved her father a lot and agreed to go stay with the Beast.
The Beast treated Beauty with a lot of kindness. He was never rude to her. He let her stay in the biggest room and let her roam in the beautiful garden. Beauty would sit near the fireplace and sew while the Beast kept her company. At first, Beauty was afraid of the Beast but slowly, she began to like him.
One day, the Beast asked Beauty to marry him, but she refused. She was still afraid of his fearful-looking face. The Beast still treated her kindly and with a lot of love. Beauty missed her father a lot. The Beast gave her a magic mirror and said, ‚ÄúLook at the mirror and you can see your family. Now you won‚Äôt feel lonely anymore.
One day, Beauty looked in the mirror and saw that father was very ill and dying. She went to the Beast and pleaded and cried, ‚ÄúPlease let me go home! I only want to see my father before he dies!‚Äù But the Beast roared, ‚ÄúNo! You promised you would never leave this castle!‚Äù Saying this, he stormed out of the room. But after some time, he came to Beauty and said, ‚ÄúYou may go to stay with your father for seven days. But you must promise to return after that.‚Äù Beauty was very happy and agreed. Then she left and went to stay with her father. Her father, on seeing Beauty, felt very happy and soon recovered. Beauty stayed with her family for seven days and more. She forgot the Beast and his castle. But one night, she had a terrible nightmare in which she saw the Beast was very ill and about to die. He was crying, ‚ÄúBeauty, please come back!‚Äù
Beauty woke up and went back to the castle because she did not mean to hurt the Beast. She cried and said, ‚ÄúPlease don‚Äôt die, Beast! I will live with you forever!‚Äù The Beast miraculously changed into a handsome prince. He said, ‚ÄúI was under a curse all these years and could only be relieved when someone fell in love with me. I am now cured of the curse because you truly love me.‚Äù And then, Beauty and the Beast were married and together they lived happily ever after.

History: 

Disneyland Paris opened its gates in 1992 and quickly became one of Europe‚Äôs most popular tourist destinations. Modeled after the original Disneyland in California, it combines classic Disney magic with a touch of European charm. Highlights include the iconic Sleeping Beauty Castle (15:53), inspired by French fairytale castles, and Main Street, U.S.A. (10:18), which transports visitors to a nostalgic small-town America at the turn of the 20th century. The park‚Äôs themed lands, like Adventureland and Discoveryland, bring to life both classic and modern Disney tales through interactive rides and immersive environments.

Tourist Tips:

Start your day at Town Square (7:35) and grab a classic photo opportunity with Donald Duck (9:18).
Stroll down Main Street, U.S.A. (10:18) for shopping and meet Winnie the Pooh (13:02) for a fun character moment.
Take your time exploring Fantasyland (19:11), where you can enjoy rides like the Carousel (23:10), navigate Alice‚Äôs Curious Labyrinth (27:20), and ride the whimsical It‚Äôs a Small World (53:46).
Discover futuristic adventures in Discoveryland (1:07:47), and try the Autopia Ride (1:15:52), where you can drive a retro-futuristic car.
Head to Frontierland (1:26:36) to board the Mark Twain River Boat (1:28:47) for a scenic ride or brave the iconic Big Thunder Mountain (1:48:16) for some thrills.
Experience the classic Pirates of the Caribbean (2:10:38) in Adventureland (2:04:47) for a swashbuckling adventure.
Don‚Äôt forget to meet characters like Geppetto (1:04:27) and revisit the enchanting Sleeping Beauty Castle (2:24:26) for the perfect fairytale ending.

Title: How to make table captions and a list of tables in word
Description:
In this video I show you how to make table captions and a list of tables in word. You firstly need to add captions and change the label option to 'Table'. Then you need to go to the references tab and select 'insert table of figures' and make sure 'Table' is selected. The tables will then be automatically renumbered and the list of tables can then be updated is the captions or page numbers change.

This is a very useful feature for writing a thesis/ dissertation.

Title: How to Turn on Closed Captions on YouTube
Description:
How to Turn on Closed Captions on YouTube
http://www.a2ztube.co (Watch Movies, TV Shows, Music Albums and Tutorials)
How to Turn on Closed Captions on YouTube?
1. Open your Favorite Browser.
2. Go to Youtube.com
3. Click Sign in Button at the Top Right Corner of the Page.
4. Enter Your Email address and password.
5. Click Sign in.
6. Search for a Video.
7. Now, Let Us Look for Videos with Closed Captions.
8. Click on a Video that you would like to watch.
9. Click on this Small Icon on the YouTube Video Player to turn on the Closed Caption.
10. As you can see, Caption Started Appearing on the Video.
11. This is How You can Turn on Closed Captions on YouTube.

Title: New Captions Workflow in Premiere Pro
Description:
Captions are now beautifully integrated into the editorial workflow in the Premiere Pro. Add captions to your Timeline and adjust the placement and duration, just as you do with other clips on the Timeline. Edit text right in the Program Monitor, use Zone Controls for positioning and stylize your captions using familiar Adobe design tools in the Essential Graphics panel. Deliver brilliant, custom-captioned video faster.

Title: How to Adjust Subtitle Speed to Sync in VLC Media Player
Description:
VLC Media Player allows you to add subtitles directly through the software. You can also adjust the timing of your subtitle to correctly sync it to your movie or show. 

To properly sync your subtitles to the audio and video you first want to distinguish the time difference in seconds. 

There are two main ways to adjust the delay of your subtitle text. Through the track synchronisation options and by using keyboard shortcuts. Track synchronisation allows you to offset the subtitle speed in seconds. Whereas using the G and H keys on your keyboard will offset the subtitle speed by 50 milliseconds.

Title: How to turn on live captions in Microsoft Teams
Description:
With live captions, Teams can detect what‚Äôs said in a meeting and present real-time captions for anyone who wants them. 

Live captions can make your meeting more inclusive to participants who are deaf or hard-of-hearing, people with different levels of language proficiency, and participants in loud places by giving them another way to follow along.

Learn more, here: https://support.office.com/en-us/article/use-live-captions-in-a-teams-meeting-4be2d304-f675-4b57-8347-cbd000a21260

Title: hearing people who hate subtitles/captions at the movie theater
Description:
AMC, Marcus, Fandango, etc. will tell you when a screening is open captioned or closed captioned on the apps and websites so be sure you know what tickets you‚Äôre buying!

Video Description:
Rikki with no makeup on (light Tiktok filter) and shoulder length brown wavy hair down. She is wearing a Chucky graphic tee. Text at top of video says, ‚ÄúHearing people disgusted by subtitles on the cinema screen?‚Äù

Transcript:
So I‚Äôm deaf and I went to go see the open caption screening of Longlegs and beside of me there was a mother and daughter. And some of the trailers had captions. Not all of them do, but after like the fourth one, the mother turns to me. She goes, ‚ÄúAre these captions gonna be on the screen like the whole time?‚Äù And I was like, ‚ÄúYeah, there is an open caption screening.‚Äù And her daughter jerks up in her seat with like this look of disgust on her face and the mother doesn‚Äôt look that happy either, and she‚Äôs picking up her phone and looking through the email like, ‚ÄúI don‚Äôt recall this being in my email,‚Äù even though it tells you, you know, before you get the ticket. I almost wanted to be like, ‚ÄúI sure hope so because I‚Äôm deaf and I need them,‚Äù just- just to see if it would get awkward for her. About Captions

Captions App offers an AI powered creative studio that‚Äôs revolutionizing how millions of creators develop content. 

With Captions‚Äô cutting-edge but easily accessible technology, it only takes a few taps for anyone anywhere to create studio-grade videos. 

With Captions App, you can automatically generate the most accurate captions for portrait, vertical, square, and landscape video formats, in over 25 languages. 

Powered by cutting-edge speech recognition technology, the app adds captions using Whisper speech-to-text by OpenAI ‚Äì the world's most powerful speech-to-text engine.

Beyond offering accuracy, Captions also offers tons of customization options ‚Äî allowing for custom fonts, colors, and animations.

Adding captions to your videos is important for a few reasons.

Accessibility ‚Äî Captions play a crucial role in making your videos more accessible. With over 6% of the world's population experiencing some degree of hearing loss, it's essential to prioritize inclusivity with your content. By adding captions, you enable individuals with hearing impairments to fully enjoy and engage with your content.

Understanding & Engagement ‚Äî Don't let your videos go unnoticed! Boost your engagement within seconds by adding dynamic captions. Research shows that 80% of viewers watch videos without sound. By incorporating captions, you ensure that your message will be effectively communicated to the maximum number of potential viewers.

SEO ‚Äî By captioning your videos, you‚Äôre creating a transcript. Search engines can easily index text, thus boosting your visibility to potentially interested viewers.

Once you‚Äôve watched and learned how to add animated captions, learn more about customizing your captions and uploading your own fonts in the next video.

Title: ROTHENBURG ob der Tauber, Germany üá©üá™ - 4K HDR with captions
Description:
Rothenburg ob der Tauber is a German town in northern Bavaria. This place is known for its old town with picturesque medieval architecture which is especially scenic during Christmas Time. Many tourists visiting Bavaria make a trip to Rothenburg to see the many preserved gate houses and towers.

We start our tour of Rothenburg at the market square and then explore the town. With a slower pace we see many parts of Rothenburg and its old walls. We even catch the "Reiterle" a rider on horseback giving Christmas greetings - a local tradition.

Enjoy Christmas time in Germany on this walk around Rothenburg ob der Tauber!

For another, longer walk through Rothenburg ob der Tauber, check out https://youtu.be/nid-1jfNMrQ

Description: I have now added captions to all my videos (but not all shorts and old streams). Having captions is obviously import for people with hearing loss, but having captions also improves search. The problem is that captioning videos used to be a lot of work. While definitely not perfect, this is a great starting point that I can manually fix and upload to YouTube. And I have now done so.
